---
description: Apply Ruff linter/formatter configuration. Use when writing or reviewing Python code.
globs: "**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---

Ruff Configuration (in pyproject.toml):
- `src = ["src", "tests"]`
- `line-length = 120`
- Rules: `B` (bugbear), `C4` (comprehensions), `E` (pycodestyle), `F` (pyflakes), `N` (naming), `W` (warnings), `I` (isort), `UP` (pyupgrade)

Workflow:
- `uv run ruff check src/ tests/` — lint
- `uv run ruff format src/ tests/` — format
- Fix auto-fixable issues: `uv run ruff check --fix`

Avoid:
- `# noqa` without specific rule code
- Disabling rules globally without justification
- Template files should be excluded from linting
